"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-02-09-paris-olympics-medals-contain-piece-eiffel-tower\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France - The medals awarded at this year's Paris Olympics and Paralympics will feature a hexagon-shaped piece of iron taken from the original Eiffel Tower in their centre, organisers said as they unveiled the design yesterday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999998955788305, \"rank\": 6.360919788208383e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PARIS\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 5}, {\"ngram\": \"The medals\", \"from\": 16, \"to\": 26}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 38, \"to\": 64}, {\"ngram\": \"Paralympics\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 80}, {\"ngram\": \"a hexagon-shaped piece\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 116}, {\"ngram\": \"iron\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 124}, {\"ngram\": \"the original Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 161}, {\"ngram\": \"their centre\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 177}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 189}, {\"ngram\": \"the design\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All 5,084 gold, silver and bronze medals for the Paris Games will feature the six-edged metal medallion, which will be set like a gemstone in the design by elite French jewellery house Chaumet.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 397, \"end\": 403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9427795219981607, \"rank\": 0.03755645754050907, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 404, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jewellery\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6297246996000055e-16, \"text\": \"jewellery\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jewellery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jewellery\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All 5,084 gold\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 249}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 257}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 268}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 275}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 295}, {\"ngram\": \"the six-edged metal medallion\", \"from\": 309, \"to\": 338}, {\"ngram\": \"a gemstone\", \"from\": 363, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"the design\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We wanted to offer to all medal winners at the Paris Olympics and Paralympics a piece of the Eiffel Tower from 1889,\\\" said the head of the local organising committee, Tony Estanguet, at a televised ceremony.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 598, \"end\": 612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all medal winners\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 470}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 492}, {\"ngram\": \"Paralympics\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 508}, {\"ngram\": \"a piece\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 516}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"the head\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 562}, {\"ngram\": \"the local organising committee\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 596}, {\"ngram\": \"a televised ceremony\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 637}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will be \\\"a combination of the most precious metals from the medals -gold, silver and bronze - with the most precious metal in our country, from this treasure that is the Eiffel Tower,\\\" he explained.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 843, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a combination\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 667}, {\"ngram\": \"the most precious metals\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 725}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"the most precious metal\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"our country\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 782}, {\"ngram\": \"this treasure\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 802}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 827}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The design by Chaumet, whose creations have adorned aristocrats and the affluent since 1780, also features a circular arrangement of ridges intended to catch the light and evoke the sun's rays.\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The design\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 855}, {\"ngram\": \"Chaumet\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 866}, {\"ngram\": \"whose creations\", \"from\": 868, \"to\": 883}, {\"ngram\": \"aristocrats\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 908}, {\"ngram\": \"the affluent\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 925}, {\"ngram\": \"a circular arrangement\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"ridges\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 984}, {\"ngram\": \"the light\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1012}, {\"ngram\": \"the sun's rays\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The iron hexagon - a shape which echoes the contours of mainland France - is held in place by six spurs on each corner which are intended to resemble the rivets used on the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1105, \"end\": 1111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999998955788305, \"rank\": 6.360919788208383e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The iron hexagon\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"a shape\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"the contours\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1130}, {\"ngram\": \"six spurs\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"each corner\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1158}, {\"ngram\": \"the rivets\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1200}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1225}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The metal was taken from a Paris warehouse used to stock offcuts by the operating company which maintains the 330-metre landmark, known affectionately as the \\\"Old Lady\\\" in France.\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1255, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.017543479568712e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1400, \"end\": 1406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999998955788305, \"rank\": 6.360919788208383e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The metal\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1237}, {\"ngram\": \"stock offcuts\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"the operating company\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"the 330-metre landmark\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1356}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"Old Lady\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1395}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We found out that over the years during the maintenance of the Eiffel Tower that they were obliged to remove some of the original structure,\\\" Thierry Reboul, the director of branding and ceremonies, explained during an advance preview of the medals.\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1552, \"end\": 1559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9444370659661287e-22, \"text\": \"Thierry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1442}, {\"ngram\": \"the maintenance\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1485}, {\"ngram\": \"the original structure\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"the director\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1580}, {\"ngram\": \"branding\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"ceremonies\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1607}, {\"ngram\": \"an advance preview\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1644}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1658}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We used these pieces.\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1683, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these pieces\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1682}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were more than enough of them.\\\"\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1721, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Medal design is a key part of each Games' aesthetic, along with the logo, mascots and opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Medal design\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1735}, {\"ngram\": \"a key part\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1749}, {\"ngram\": \"the logo\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1795}, {\"ngram\": \"mascots\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1804}, {\"ngram\": \"opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since 2004, the back of all medals show the Greek goddess Nike flying into the historic Panathinaikos stadium in Athens, site of the original Olympic Games of antiquity.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1872, \"end\": 1877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_